Initially, there were 36 children on the bus.  68 children got off, so there were 36 - 68 = -32 children. This means there were no children left on the bus, and in fact 32 *more* children got off than were on the bus to begin with.

After the 68 children got off and some got on, there were 12 children on the bus.  Since there were effectively 0 children on the bus after the 68 got off, this means 12 children got on.

The difference between the number of children who got off and the number who got on is 68 - 12 = 56.

Answer: {56}
